      "writtenOn": "2017-07-06T18:54:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the lambda invocation is pretty straightforward:\n\n    void constructImpl(internal::Seq\u003cS...\u003e) const {\n\u003e\u003e\u003e\u003e   auto args \u003d mCtorArgsGetter(); \u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\n\nWe store the lambda into |mCtorArgsGetter| member. MemberOnDemandT\u003c\u003e alias explicitly forces |mCtorArgsGetter| to be not a lambda but std::function\u003c\u003e that stores that lambda  inside - which is less efficient but the type is known at declaration time.\nAt the time of on-demand construction this class calls stored lambda to get constructor parameters, then unpacks them to call T\u0027s constructor. And this is what is complicated and explained in the \u0027template magic\u0027 comment",
